  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Attributes</h2>
    <table class="props-table">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Attribute</th>
          <th>Description</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td><code>dir</code></td>
          <td><strong>Required.</strong> Text direction: <code>ltr</code> (left-to-right) or <code>rtl</code> (right-to-left)</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
    <p>Also supports <a href="/docs/elements/native/states/">global attributes</a>.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>CSS</h2>
    <code-block language="css" label="bdo CSS (browser default)">{{ bdoCssCode | escape }}</code-block>
    <p>VB does not add additional styling. The element's value is in its Unicode override behavior.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Accessibility</h2>
    <p><code>&lt;bdo&gt;</code> affects visual presentation only. Screen readers typically read text in logical order, not visual order. Be cautious using <code>&lt;bdo&gt;</code> purely for visual effects, as the rendered order may confuse users who cannot see it.</p>
  </section>

